You must not feel, Mamma, that you are in any sense at all a burden on me. I am beginning to wish I had done and coudl do very very much more for you. I am grateful to know that after all the hard years you are steadily attaining more wisdom and insight. It is a genuine triumph, the only significant triumph possible, I have no doubt. Yes, outdoors is the place for you. Often when I see a few trees alone and a little grass that flash of understanding comes. But it can't stay long in such conditions as I live in. I don't mean at home. Home is more harmonious than ever. and we have no real trouble of any sort. Sig and I are genuine friends and will be more so. 
